<div class="inner-page">

  <!-- Hero Banner -->
  <div class="page-hero" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1B4332 0%,#2D6A4F 100%);">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:#52B788;">The Ingredients</div>
      <h1 style="color:#fff;">Meet the Mushrooms</h1>
      <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8);max-width:560px;margin:0 auto;">Three of nature's most studied functional mushrooms. Dual-extracted for full potency. In every single can.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Mushroom 1: Lion's Mane -->
  <section class="mush-section">
    <div class="mush-inner">
      <div class="mush-badge" style="background:#EEF2FF;color:#3730A3;">FOCUS</div>
      <div class="mush-layout">
        <div class="mush-icon-wrap" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#EEF2FF,#C7D2FE);">
          <div class="mush-emoji">🧠</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mush-content">
          <h2>Lion's Mane</h2>
          <div class="mush-dose">900mg per can · Fruiting body extract</div>
          <p class="mush-desc">Lion's Mane (<em>Hericium erinaceus</em>) is the nootropic mushroom. It's been used in traditional medicine for centuries — now modern research is catching up to why.</p>
          <div class="mush-benefits">
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">🔬</span><div><strong>Nerve Growth Factor (NGF)</strong><p>Lion's Mane stimulates the production of NGF — a protein critical for the growth, maintenance, and survival of nerve cells. More NGF means better neural connectivity.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">💡</span><div><strong>Cognitive Clarity</strong><p>Clinical studies show Lion's Mane supplementation improves memory, focus, and mild cognitive function. The effect is subtle but consistent — like sharpening a lens.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">🛡️</span><div><strong>Neuroprotection</strong><p>Emerging research shows Lion's Mane may help protect against age-related cognitive decline by supporting myelin sheath integrity.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mush-fact">
            <strong>Why 900mg?</strong> Most studies showing cognitive benefit used doses of 500–3,000mg daily. At 900mg per can, Happie hits an effective daily dose in a single serving.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mush-divider"></div>

  <!-- Mushroom 2: Cordyceps -->
  <section class="mush-section" style="background:#FAFAFA;">
    <div class="mush-inner">
      <div class="mush-badge" style="background:#FFF7ED;color:#C2410C;">ENERGY</div>
      <div class="mush-layout">
        <div class="mush-icon-wrap" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#FFF7ED,#FED7AA);">
          <div class="mush-emoji">⚡</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mush-content">
          <h2>Cordyceps</h2>
          <div class="mush-dose">700mg per can · Cordyceps militaris · Fruiting body extract</div>
          <p class="mush-desc">Cordyceps (<em>Cordyceps militaris</em>) is the energy mushroom — used by Tibetan herders for altitude endurance and by elite athletes for performance. No caffeine. No adrenal crash.</p>
          <div class="mush-benefits">
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">🫁</span><div><strong>Oxygen Utilization (VO2 Max)</strong><p>Cordyceps increases the body's production of ATP — the molecule that powers cellular energy. Studies show improved VO2 max and oxygen uptake efficiency in athletes.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">🏃</span><div><strong>Endurance Without Stimulants</strong><p>Unlike caffeine, Cordyceps doesn't spike cortisol. It works at the mitochondrial level — more efficient energy production means sustained output without the 2pm crash.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">💪</span><div><strong>Exercise Recovery</strong><p>Cordyceps has been shown to reduce exercise-induced fatigue and support faster recovery by buffering lactic acid buildup in muscle tissue.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mush-fact">
            <strong>Militaris, not sinensis.</strong> We use <em>Cordyceps militaris</em> — the cultivated species with the highest concentration of Cordycepin, the key active compound. <em>C. sinensis</em> (the parasitic caterpillar fungus) is rare, expensive, and inconsistent.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mush-divider"></div>

  <!-- Mushroom 3: Reishi -->
  <section class="mush-section">
    <div class="mush-inner">
      <div class="mush-badge" style="background:#F0FDF4;color:#166534;">CALM</div>
      <div class="mush-layout">
        <div class="mush-icon-wrap" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#F0FDF4,#BBF7D0);">
          <div class="mush-emoji">🌿</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mush-content">
          <h2>Reishi</h2>
          <div class="mush-dose">400mg per can · Ganoderma lucidum · Fruiting body extract</div>
          <p class="mush-desc">Reishi (<em>Ganoderma lucidum</em>) is known as the "mushroom of immortality" in traditional Chinese medicine. The adaptogen that brings everything into balance.</p>
          <div class="mush-benefits">
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">🧘</span><div><strong>Stress Adaptation</strong><p>Reishi's triterpenes help modulate the HPA axis — your body's stress response system. Regular use helps your body respond to stress more efficiently rather than overreacting.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">😴</span><div><strong>Sleep Quality</strong><p>Studies show Reishi can improve sleep latency and total sleep time by supporting GABAergic pathways — the same mechanisms targeted by many sleep medications, but naturally.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mush-benefit"><span class="mush-benefit-icon">🛡️</span><div><strong>Immune Modulation</strong><p>Reishi's beta-glucans are among the most studied immunomodulatory compounds in nature. They don't just boost immunity — they help regulate it for optimal function.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mush-fact">
            <strong>The balance mushroom.</strong> While Lion's Mane sharpens and Cordyceps energizes, Reishi keeps you grounded. Together, the three create a stack that's focused and energized — without the edge.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Extraction method callout -->
  <section style="background:var(--green-dark);padding:80px 24px;">
    <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;text-align:center;">
      <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:#52B788;">Our Standard</div>
      <h2 style="color:#fff;font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px);font-weight:900;margin-bottom:20px;">Dual-Extracted. Fruiting Body Only.</h2>
      <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8);font-size:17px;line-height:1.7;max-width:680px;margin:0 auto 40px;">Most mushroom products use mycelium grown on grain — which is mostly starch with minimal active compounds. We use <strong style="color:#fff;">100% fruiting body extracts</strong>, dual-extracted with hot water and alcohol to capture both water-soluble beta-glucans and fat-soluble triterpenes.</p>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:24px;max-width:700px;margin:0 auto;">
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:16px;padding:24px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
          <div style="font-size:28px;margin-bottom:8px;">🍄</div>
          <strong style="color:#fff;display:block;margin-bottom:6px;">Fruiting Body</strong>
          <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);font-size:13px;">The actual mushroom — not grain-grown mycelium</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:16px;padding:24px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
          <div style="font-size:28px;margin-bottom:8px;">💧</div>
          <strong style="color:#fff;display:block;margin-bottom:6px;">Dual Extracted</strong>
          <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);font-size:13px;">Hot water + alcohol extraction for full spectrum</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:16px;padding:24px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
          <div style="font-size:28px;margin-bottom:8px;">✅</div>
          <strong style="color:#fff;display:block;margin-bottom:6px;">Third-Party Tested</strong>
          <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);font-size:13px;">Every batch verified for potency and purity</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="padding:80px 24px;text-align:center;background:var(--cream);">
    <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,40px);font-weight:900;margin-bottom:16px;">Ready to feel it yourself?</h2>
    <p style="font-size:17px;color:var(--gray);margin-bottom:32px;">2,000mg per can. Three flavors. One mission.</p>
    <a href="/collections/all" class="btn-primary btn-lg">Shop All Flavors →</a>
  </section>

</div>

<style>
.inner-page { }
.page-hero { padding: 80px 24px; text-align: center; }
.page-hero-inner { max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; }
.page-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(36px,5vw,60px); font-weight: 900; margin: 12px 0 16px; }
.mush-section { padding: 80px 24px; background: #fff; }
.mush-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
.mush-badge { display: inline-block; border-radius: 50px; padding: 5px 16px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-bottom: 28px; }
.mush-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr; gap: 60px; align-items: start; }
.mush-icon-wrap { border-radius: 24px; width: 280px; height: 280px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; }
.mush-emoji { font-size: 100px; }
.mush-content h2 { font-size: clamp(32px,4vw,48px); font-weight: 900; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.mush-dose { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--green); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 18px; }
.mush-desc { font-size: 16px; color: #444; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 28px; }
.mush-benefits { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
.mush-benefit { display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start; }
.mush-benefit-icon { font-size: 22px; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
.mush-benefit strong { display: block; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.mush-benefit p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
.mush-fact { background: var(--green-light); border-radius: 14px; padding: 18px 22px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--green-dark); line-height: 1.6; border-left: 4px solid var(--green); }
.mush-divider { height: 1px; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.06); }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .mush-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .mush-icon-wrap { width: 160px; height: 160px; }
  .mush-emoji { font-size: 60px; }
}
</style>

